Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Health authorities are urging people to continue obeying lockdown rules. This over fears of a third wave of COVID-19 infections in Gauteng. New cases have been increasing significantly since last week. READ: First batch of Pfizer vaccines arrive in South Africa The Gauteng Health Department says outbreaks are being recorded in Vereeniging, parts of Tshwane, and parts of Johannesburg. Data modelling by the National Institute for Communicable Diseases says Gauteng will be the hardest-hit province, and a third wave would be more devastating than the second.